        public PolyClassPart(java.lang.String identifier,
                     int visibility,
                     boolean mfr_static,
                     boolean mfr_constant,
                     boolean mfr_abstract)
              throws java.lang.NullPointerException
        Constructs a new class part with no modifiers.

        Sets the identifier, visibility, and modifiers for this class part.

        The identifier parameter MAY NOT BE NULL, this will throw a NullPointerException.

        The visibility parameter may be 0, 1, 2, or 3 which mean no visibility, private, protected, or public, respectively.

        Parameters:
        identifier - name of this part of the class
        visibility - visibility of this part of the class
        mfr_static - sets the static status of this part of the class
        mfr_constant - sets the constant status of this part of the class
        mfr_abstract - sets the abstract status of this part of the class
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException
